				Well, now I want to know more about the book!  We've had teasers=
 about it for some time now, but give us the skinny on it=2E

Is it going to be just a collection of cases like this blog, or=
 more a "autobiography" of you work experiences?  

I would really like to see exactly what you have in the blog, but=
 then go over a "summary" of each case and describe the technical=
 aspects of it to answer all those questions that you know we've=
 been asking=2E  Such as:  What/who is Roscoe and how is he setup;=
 What tools/systems did you use during that case; Possibly=
 explain the procedures and more indepth=2E


